subSubSection.paragraph:
Gonopods (
Figs 7
; 
8
) very simple. Coxae subquadrate, large, microtuberculate and abundantly setose ventrolaterally, with a conspicuous rounded lobe frontolaterally. Telopodite considerably longer than coxite, slightly stouter, setose in its basal half, with an inconspicuous, digitiform, simple, lateral, distofemoral process (dp) at about midway, more distally with a slightly folded and enlarged shaft (= solenomere) with dense pilosity and a hairpad; seminal groove terminating subapically, acropodite short.
